text: Sir Alexander Penrose Cumming-Gordon, 1st Baronet (19 May 1749 – 10 February 1806) was a Scottish politician. Cumming-Gordon sat as Member of Parliament (MP) for Inverness Burghs from 1802 to 1803. In 1804 he was created a baronet, of Altyre near Forres. His second son Charles Cumming-Bruce was also a politician. ==References== * * == External links == * Category:1749 births Category:1806 deaths Category:Baronets in the Baronetage of the United Kingdom Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for Scottish constituencies Category:UK MPs 1802–1806
